text=(:nogroupheader:)%0a(:Summary::)%0a(:Published::)%0a(:Author:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:License:[[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Res_communis|Site License]]:)%0a(:Update::)%0a(:Maintainer:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:Creator:[[]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!Cryptics]]:)%0a(:Also:none:)%0a(:Archive:[[|Archive.is]], [[|Archive.org]]:)%0a(:Download:[[{$FullName}?action=print|URL]],[[https://www.web2pdfconvert.com/|PDF from URL]]:)%0a%0aSee also [[Bank coin]].  Banks have been given the green light to offer custody services by the comptroller of the currency [[https://www.occ.treas.gov/topics/charters-and-licensing/interpretations-and-actions/2020/int1170.pdf|#]]%0a%0a!!Ransomware preparation%0a%0aPrior to offering an digital storage solutions for customers the bank must create a defense plan against ransomware attacks and also a ransomware response policy in the event they are hit with an attack.  These risks and the response policy should be agreed to by those requesting digital storage from the bank.%0a%0a%0a!!Document storage [[#doc]]%0a%0aBanks can offer secure digital storage space for clients.  This can be given as a perk for an account at a bank.  For savings accounts maintain a certain balance to get higher storage capacity.%0a%0aBanks can use zero knowledge encrypted storage like this [[https://tresorit.com/|#]] to keep customers data secure and fully private.%0a%0aHaving zero knowledge of the data stored by the customer is very ideal as to prevent the bank from becoming a honeypot for government spying on the customers [[https://zycrypto.com/the-irs-is-looking-to-seize-billions-of-dollars-worth-of-cryptocurrency-in-2022/|#]].%0a!!Balance view%0a%0aThe bank could simply use a 3rd party or in-house block explorer to display someones personal crypto holdings in dollar equivalent. These holdings could be custodied by the person entirely or partially or fully by the bank.%0a%0aThis balance should be denoted as "unverified balance" unless the person signs for the public key.%0a%0a!!Non-Fiduciary Custody%0a%0aFor non-fiduciary custody the bank should not be given the authority to prevent, freeze, or send the funds without the customers approval otherwise it can become a honeypot for government regulators [[https://zycrypto.com/the-irs-is-looking-to-seize-billions-of-dollars-worth-of-cryptocurrency-in-2022/|#]].%0a%0a!!!Non-custodial%0a%0aAka "custody assistance"%0a%0a!!!!Passphrase wallet%0a%0aThe bank could hold an encrypted wallet file and the person could hold the passphrase to sign transactions.  This is also easy to do with simple [[#doc|document storage]]%0a%0a!!!!Multisig wallet%0a%0aCreating a multisig wallet and applications [[https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Multi-signature|#]]%0a%0a2 of 3 from bitcoin core [[https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/24794/how-can-i-use-multi-signature-addresses-with-bitcoin-core|#]] you hold 2 bank holds 1.  This would be to ensure that if you loose a key the bank has one saved for you.  It is suggested the owner holds one key and the executor of the estate the other.  And the bank will only provide their private key upon request of the person themselves or in the case of their passing, the executor of the estate.%0a%0a3 of 4. You hold 3 the bank holds 1.  %0a%0aThe bank should never hold enough keys to prevent a transaction (2 of 2 wallet for example where the bank holds one of the two keys).  If they did the cryptocurrency would be censorable by the bank or government regulators.  Also a 1 of 2 or something similar should never be used with a bank since the bank could move your funds without permission.%0a%0a%0a%0a!!!Custodial%0a%0a%0a!!!!Cold storage%0aThe bank could hold all of the keys and have them in cold offline storage and thus would not be able to offer interest (since the bank could not use them to invest) but would be able to offer loans using the coins as collateral.%0a%0a!!Fiduciary Custody%0a%0aThe bank could hold all the keys and in exchange for the customer basically loaning the bank crypto, the bank could offer fiat loans to the customer backed by the crypto or give them interest in either crypto or fiat.%0a%0a!!Rewards%0a%0aThe bank can either create their own token that they can distribute to customers when certain requirements are met or more preferably a bank could create their own blockchain coin ([[bank coin]]) or adopt an existing one and mine it themselves (and allow anyone else to mine) and give it as a reward to customers for holding deposits in their bank.
